{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJ1NgAVwJHDB2BEcyQtE2k","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task 18: Vertical Slice Tests\n2\t\n3\t## Description\n4\t\n5\tImplement the 10 full-stack integration test scenarios from `08-TESTING.md`. These are end-to-end tests that exercise the complete system: API server, Scheduler, Host Wrapper, MCP Server, and mock agent — all running together via Docker Compose. They validate that the components integrate correctly and that the system works as a whole.\n6\t\n7\tThese tests run against a real platform instance (spun up by `ci-instance.sh`) and use the mock agent binary instead of real LLM hosts. They are compiled as a separate test crate (`crates/vertical-tests/`) and executed in CI Stage 3.\n8\t\n9\t## Deliverables\n10\t\n11\t### Test crate setup\n12\t\n13\t- `crates/vertical-tests/Cargo.toml` — test crate, `publish = false`. Dependencies: `tokio`, `reqwest`, `serde_json`, `uuid`, `common` (workspace dependency), `tracing`, `tracing-subscriber`\n14\t- `crates/vertical-tests/src/lib.rs` — shared test helpers\n15\t- `crates/vertical-tests/tests/` — one test file per scenario (or grouped logically)\n16\t\n17\t### Test helper (`crates/vertical-tests/src/lib.rs`)\n18\t\n19\tShared utilities for all vertical slice tests:\n20\t\n21\t- `TestClient` struct:\n22\t  - `base_url: String` — platform API base URL (from `AGENT_FARM_TEST_URL` env var, default `http://localhost:18081`)\n23\t  - `http: reqwest::Client`\n24\t  - `admin_token: String` — JWT access token for the test admin user\n25\t\n26\t- `TestClient::new() -> Self` — reads base_url from env, creates HTTP client\n27\t\n28\t- `TestClient::setup_admin() -> Result<String, TestError>` — creates a test admin user by:\n29\t  1. Directly inserting a user + identity into the database (bypassing OAuth)\n30\t  2. Issuing a JWT access token for the user\n31\t  3. Returning the access token\n32\t  - Implementation: The vertical tests need a way to seed users and get tokens without going through OAuth. Options:\n33\t    a. A test-only admin endpoint `POST /internal/test/seed-user` (only available when `AGENT_FARM_TEST_MODE=true`)\n34\t    b. Direct database insertion via `DATABASE_URL` (the test crate connects to Postgres directly)\n35\t  - Use option (b): connect directly to Postgres, insert user with admin role, insert identity, and use the platform's token issuance endpoint (or sign a JWT directly using the test keys).\n36\t\n37\t- `TestClient::create_agent(token: &str, name: &str, prompt: &str) -> Result<AgentResponse, TestError>`\n38\t- `TestClient::create_team(token: &str, name: &str) -> Result<TeamResponse, TestError>`\n39\t- `TestClient::create_inbox(token: &str, team_id: Uuid, name: &str, agent_id: Uuid, retry_count: i32) -> Result<InboxResponse, TestError>`\n40\t- `TestClient::submit_task(token: &str, team_id: Uuid, inbox_id: Uuid, body: &str, sink: &SinkConfig) -> Result<TaskResponse, TestError>`\n41\t- `TestClient::get_task(token: &str, task_id: Uuid) -> Result<TaskResponse, TestError>`\n42\t- `TestClient::get_job(token: &str, root_task_id: Uuid) -> Result<JobDetailResponse, TestError>`\n43\t- `TestClient::wait_for_task_status(token: &str, task_id: Uuid, expected: TaskStatus, timeout: Duration) -> Result<TaskResponse, TestError>` — polls the task endpoint until the status matches or timeout expires\n44\t- `TestClient::wait_for_job_status(token: &str, root_task_id: Uuid, expected: JobStatus, timeout: Duration) -> Result<JobDetailResponse, TestError>` — polls the job endpoint\n45\t- `TestClient::set_llm_api_key(token: &str, provider: &str, key: &str) -> Result<(), TestError>` — sets a (mock) LLM API key\n46\t- `TestClient::connect_sink(token: &str, provider: &str) -> Result<(), TestError>` — sets up sink credentials (directly in DB for testing)\n47\t- `TestClient::connect_sse(token: &str, path: &str) -> Result<SseStream, TestError>` — connects to an SSE endpoint and returns a stream\n48\t\n49\t- `SseStream` struct — wraps an `reqwest::Response` providing `async fn next_event() -> Option<SseEvent>`\n50\t- `SseEvent` struct: `event_type: String`, `data: serde_json::Value`, `id: Option<String>`\n51\t\n52\t- `setup_test_sink_repo() -> Result<TestSinkRepo, TestError>` — creates a local bare git repo and an initial commit. Returns the repo path (used as sink_repo_url in file:// protocol for local testing).\n53\t- `TestSinkRepo` struct: `bare_repo_path: String`, `branch: String`\n54\t- `TestSinkRepo::has_commit(&self, message_contains: &str) -> bool` — checks if the bare repo has a commit containing the given string\n55\t- `TestSinkRepo::has_branch(&self, name: &str) -> bool`\n56\t- `TestSinkRepo::cleanup(&self)` — removes temp directories\n57\t\n58\t- `TestError` enum with descriptive variants\n59\t\n60\t### Scenario 1: Single-task completion (`tests/single_task.rs`)\n61\t\n62\t1. Setup: create admin user, agent, team, inbox, set credentials, create local bare git sink repo\n63\t2. Submit a root task with the local sink repo\n64\t3. Wait for task status to become Completed (timeout: 60s)\n65\t4. Get the task and verify:\n66\t   - `status` is Completed\n67\t   - `result_summary` is populated (from mock agent)\n68\t   - `started_at` and `completed_at` are set\n69\t5. Get the job and verify:\n70\t   - Job status is Succeeded\n71\t   - `commit_sha` is populated (commit was pushed)\n72\t6. Verify the sink repo has a new commit\n73\t\n74\t### Scenario 2: Multi-stage pipeline — 3 inboxes (`tests/multi_stage.rs`)\n75\t\n76\t1. Setup: create agent, team with 3 inboxes (inbox-1, inbox-2, inbox-3), each subscribed to the same agent but mock agent configured to chain:\n77\t   - inbox-1 mock agent: `MOCK_AGENT_CHILD_TASK_BODY=\"Step 2 work\"`, `MOCK_AGENT_CHILD_INBOX_NAME=\"inbox-2\"`\n78\t   - inbox-2 mock agent: `MOCK_AGENT_CHILD_TASK_BODY=\"Step 3 work\"`, `MOCK_AGENT_CHILD_INBOX_NAME=\"inbox-3\"`\n79\t   - inbox-3 mock agent: completes normally (no child)\n80\t   \n81\t   Note: 