id, expected: JobStatus, timeout: Duration) -> Result<JobDetailResponse, TestError>` — polls the job endpoint\n- `TestClient::set_llm_api_key(token: &str, provider: &str, key: &str) -> Result<(), TestError>` — sets a (mock) LLM API key\n- `TestClient::connect_sink(token: &str, provider: &str) -> Result<(), TestError>` — sets up sink credentials (directly in DB for testing)\n- `TestClient::connect_sse(token: &str, path: &str) -> Result<SseStream, TestError>` — connects to an SSE endpoint and returns a stream\n\n- `SseStream` struct — wraps an `reqwest::Response` providing `async fn next_event() -> Option<SseEvent>`\n- `SseEvent` struct: `event_type: String`, `data: serde_json::Value`, `id: Option<String>`\n\n- `setup_test_sink_repo() -> Result<TestSinkRepo, TestError>` — creates a local bare git repo and an initial commit. Returns the repo path (used as sink_repo_url in file:// protocol for local testing).\n- `TestSinkRepo` struct: `bare_repo_path: String`, `branch: String`\n- `TestSinkRepo::has_commit(&self, message_contains: &str) -> bool` — checks if the bare repo has a commit containing the given string\n- `TestSinkRepo::has_branch(&self, name: &str) -> bool`\n- `TestSinkRepo::cleanup(&self)` — removes temp directories\n\n- `TestError` enum with descriptive variants\n\n### Scenario 1: Single-task completion (`tests/single_task.rs`)\n\n1. Setup: create admin user, agent, team, inbox, set credentials, create local bare git sink repo\n2. Submit a root task with the local sink repo\n3. Wait for task status to become Completed (timeout: 60s)\n4. Get the task and verify:\n   - `status` is Completed\n   - `result_summary` is populated (from mock agent)\n   - `started_at` and `completed_at` are set\n5. Get the job and verify:\n   - Job status is Succeeded\n   - `commit_sha` is populated (commit was pushed)\n6. Verify the sink repo has a new commit\n\n### Scenario 2: Multi-stage pipeline — 3 inboxes (`tests/multi_stage.rs`)\n\n1. Setup: create agent, team with 3 inboxes (