e lifetime in seconds\n```\n\n**Token Verification**:\n- Verifies against current public key\n- Falls back to previous public key if current verification fails\n- Rejects expired tokens (validates `exp` claim)\n\n---\n\n### 12. PAGINATION DETAILS\n\n**Cursor Format**: Base64-encoded `timestamp|uuid` pairs\n- Used for all list endpoints\n- Query parameter: `cursor` (optional, for pages after first)\n- Query parameter: `limit` (default varies, typically 20-100, capped at max)\n- Response field: `next_cursor` (null when no more results)\n\n---\n\n### 13. ERROR RESPONSE FORMAT\n\n```rust\npub struct ErrorResponse {\n    pub error: ErrorBody,\n}\n\npub struct ErrorBody {\n    pub code: String,      // e.g., \"not_found\", \"unauthorized\", \"validation_failed\"\n    pub message: String,\n}\n```\n\n**Common Status Codes**:\n```\n200 OK\n201 Created\n204 No Content\n400 Bad Request\n401 Unauthorized\n403 Forbidden\n404 Not Found\n409 Conflict\n429 Too Many Requests\n500 Internal Server Error\n```\n\n---\n\n### 14. SPECIAL NOTES FOR INTEGRATION TESTS\n\n**Token Generation**:\n- Tokens are signed with RS256 using the private key from `AGENT_FARM_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY`\n- Access tokens expire in exactly 15 minutes (900 seconds)\n- Instance tokens have configurable lifetime set at creation time\n\n**Encryption**:\n- Credentials (sink OAuth tokens, LLM API keys) are encrypted with AES at rest\n- Uses `AGENT_FARM_ENCRYPTION_KEY_CURRENT` and optional previous key for rotation\n\n**Refresh Tokens & SP Tokens**:\n- Opaque 32-byte random base64url-encoded strings\n- Stored as SHA-256 hashes in database\n- Tokens are never returned except at creation/regeneration\n\n**Task Chain**:\n- All tasks in a job share the same `root_task_id`\n- Parent-child relationships tracked via `parent_task_id` and `child_task_id`\n- `JobStatus` is derived from the status of all tasks in the chain\n\n**Default Clients** (seeded in migrations):\n```\nid='cli' → CLI\nid='web' → Web UI\nid='web-live' → Web UI (Li