{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pu83J9SEJAt2TonKkonsLK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive coverage of the codebase. Let me compile a thorough report.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: agent_farm Codebase\n\nI've thoroughly explored the agent_farm codebase. Here's a complete technical breakdown of all five components:\n\n---\n\n### 1. crates/mock-agent/ - How the Mock Agent Works\n\n**Purpose**: A test double for the real Claude Code / Cursor CLI agent that can simulate different agent behaviors.\n\n**Configuration** (environment variables from `config.rs`):\n- `MOCK_AGENT_MODE`: Sets behavior (complete, fail, crash, exit_non_zero, hang)\n- `MOCK_AGENT_RESULT_SUMMARY`: Optional message on completion\n- `MOCK_AGENT_CHILD_TASK_BODY`: If set, creates a child task instead of completing\n- `MOCK_AGENT_CHILD_INBOX_NAME`: Required when creating child tasks\n- `MOCK_AGENT_FAIL_REASON`: Reason string for failures\n- `MOCK_AGENT_HANG_SECONDS`: Duration to hang (if omitted, hangs indefinitely)\n- `MOCK_AGENT_WRITE_FILE`: Relative path to write a file\n- `MOCK_AGENT_WRITE_CONTENT`: Content to write to file\n- `MOCK_AGENT_DELAY_MS`: Milliseconds to delay before completing\n\n**MCP Tools Called**:\n1. **complete_task** - Args: `{result_summary?: string}` - marks task done\n2. **complete_task_and_create_next** - Args: `{target_inbox_id?: uuid, target_inbox_name?: string, task_body: string, result_summary?: string}` - complete current + spawn child task\n3. **fail_task** - Args: `{reason: string}` - fail the current task\n\n**How it Works** (`main.rs`):\n1. Reads config from environment\n2. If mode is `Crash`, emits startup event then calls `process.abort()`\n3. Reads MCP server configuration from `.mcp.json` file in `AGENT_FARM_JOB_DIR` (under `mcpServers.agent-farm`)\n4. Connects to MCP server via stdio (spawns process with command from config)\n5. Sends initialization and notifications\n6. Depending on mode:\n   - **Complete**: Optionally writes file, delays, then calls appropriate tool\n   - **Fail**: Emits thinking event, calls fail_task\n   - **ExitNonZero**: Exits with code 1\n   - **Hang**: Sleeps indefinitely (or for specified duration)\n\n**MCP Connection** (`mcp_client.rs`):\n- Spawns MCP server binary as child process with stdio pipes\n- Uses JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdin/stdout\n- Sends request, reads response line-by-line\n- Manages request IDs sequentially\n\n**Output Events** (`output.rs`):\nEmits JSON events to stdout:\n```json\n{\"type\": \"system\", \"content\": \"...\"}      // Startup\n{\"type\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"...\"}   // Thinking\n{\"type\": \"tool_use\", \"name\": \"...\", \"input\": {...}}  // Tool call\n{\"type\": \"tool_result\", \"name\": \"...\", \"content\": \"...\"} // Result\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. crates/mcp-server/ - MCP Tools Exposed\n\n**Complete Tool Definitions**:\n\n#### Tool 1: `complete_task`\n- **Schema**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"result_summary\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n    },\n    \"additionalProperties\": false\n  }\n  ```\n- **Handler**: Calls API endpoint `POST /internal/tasks/{task_id}/complete` with result_summary\n- **Response**: `{\"status\":\"completed\"}`\n\n#### Tool 2: `complete_task_and_create_next`\n- **Schema**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"target_inbox_id\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"format\": \"uuid\" },\n      \"target_inbox_name\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n      \"task_body\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n      \"result_summary\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n    },\n    \"required\": [\"task_body\"],\n    \"additionalProperties\": false\n  }\n  ```\n- **Validation**: Requires at least one of target_inbox_id or target_inbox_name\n- **Handler**: Calls API endpoint `POST /internal/tasks/{task_id}/complete-and-create-next`\n- **Response**: Returns the API response JSON (contains child task details)\n\n#### Tool 3: `fail_task`\n- **Schema**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"reason\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n    },\n    \"required\": [\"reason\"],\n    \"additionalProperties\": false\n  }\n  ```\n- **Handler**: Calls API endpoint `POST /internal/tasks/{task_id}/fail`\n- **Response**: `{\"status\":\"failed\"}`\n\n#### Tool 4: `get_task_context`\n- **Schema**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"include_bodies\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": true }\n    },\n    \"additionalProperties\": false\n  }\n  ```\n- **Handler**: Calls API endpoint `GET /internal/tasks/{task_id}/context?include_bodies={bool}`\n- **Response**: Formatted task context chain with task_id, inbox_name, result_summary\n\n#### Tool 5: `query_logs`\n- **Schema**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"task_id\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"format\": \"uuid\" },\n      \"category\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"llm\", \"operational\"] },\n      \"since\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"format\": \"date-time\" },\n      \"until\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"format\": \"date-time\" },\n      \"limit\": { \"type\": \"number\", \"default\": 100 }\n    },\n    \"additionalProperties\": false\n  }\n  ```\n- **Handler**: Calls API endpoint `GET /internal/jobs/{root_task_id}/logs?...query_params...`\n- **Response**: Formatted logs with timestamp, task_id, category\n\n**Configuration** (`config.rs`):\n- `AGENT_FARM_API_URL`: Base URL of API server\n- `AGENT_FARM_TOKEN_ENDPOINT`: Where to fetch tokens\n- `AGENT_FARM_TOKEN_SECRET`: Secret for token requests\n- `AGENT_FARM_TASK_ID`: Current task UUID\n- `AGENT_FARM_ROOT_TASK_ID`: Root job UUID\n\n**Protocol** (`protocol.rs`):\n- JSON-RPC 2.0 compliant\n- Request format: `{jsonrpc:\"2.0\", id, method, params}`\n- Response format: `{jsonrpc:\"2.0\", id, result/error}`\n- Tool responses wrapped in McpToolCallResult with content array\n\n**Transport** (`transport.rs`):\n- Reads JSON-RPC messages from stdin (line-by-line)\n- Handles methods: `initialize`, `notifications/initialized`, `tools/list`, `tools/call`\n- Writes JSON-RPC responses to stdout\n- Tool errors returned as: `{content: [{type:\"text\", text:error}], isError: true}`\n\n---\n\n### 3. crates/host-wrapper/ - Agent Invocation & Job Setup\n\n**Configuration** (`config.rs`):\nReads from environment variables:\n```rust\npub struct HostWrapperConfig {\n    pub api_url: String,                      // AGENT_FARM_API_URL\n    pub instance_id: Uuid,                    // AGENT_FARM_INSTANCE_ID\n    pub instance_token: String,               // AGENT_FARM_INSTANCE_TOKEN\n    pub instance_timeout_secs: u64,           // AGENT_FARM_INSTANCE_TIMEOUT\n    pub token_secret: String,                 // AGENT_FARM_TOKEN_SECRET\n    pub task_id: Uuid,                        // AGENT_FARM_TASK_ID\n    pub root_task_id: Uuid,                   // AGENT_FARM_ROOT_TASK_ID\n    pub llm_host: LlmHost,                    // AGENT_FARM_LLM_HOST (claude_code|cursor_cli)\n    pub llm_host_bin: String,                 // AGENT_FARM_LLM_HOST_BIN\n    pub mcp_server_bin: String,               // AGENT_FARM_MCP_SERVER_BIN\n    pub job_dir: String,                      // AGENT_FARM_JOB_DIR\n    pub heartbeat_interval_secs: u64,         // AGENT_FARM_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL (default 30)\n    pub graceful_shutdown_timeout_secs: u64,  // AGENT_FARM_GRACEFUL_SHUTDOWN_TIMEOUT (default 30)\n    pub system_prompt: String,                // AGENT_FARM_SYSTEM_PROMPT\n    pub agent_prompt: String,                 // AGENT_FARM_AGENT_PROMPT\n    pub task_body: String,                    // AGENT_FARM_TASK_BODY\n}\n```\n\n**Main Flow** (`main.rs`):\n1. Parse config from environment\n2. Create TokenManager with initial token + secret\n3. Start token server (binds to localhost:0, returns dynamic port)\n4. Write MCP config file (.mcp.json or .cursor-mcp.json in job_dir)\n5. POST `/internal/instances/{instance_id}/started` to signal startup\n6. Spawn LLM host binary as child process (with stdio piped)\n7. Parse logs and capture them in circular buffer\n8. Start background tasks:\n   - Log capture loop: reads child stdout, parses events, buffers logs\n   - Log flush loop: periodically POSTs buffered logs to `/internal/instances/{instance_id}/logs`\n   - Heartbeat loop: POSTs `/internal/instances/{instance_id}/heartbeat` every N seconds\n   - Token refresh loop: refreshes token via `/internal/instances/{instance_id}/refresh-token`\n   - Shutdown handler: waits for child process\n9. Monitor child process for exit\n10. On exit: flush remaining logs, POST `/internal/instances/{instance_id}/exited`\n\n**LLM Host Invocation** (`llm_host.rs`):\nSpawns with these arguments:\n```bash\n{llm_host_bin} \\\n  --output-format stream-json \\\n  --system-prompt \"{system_prompt}\" \\\n  --append-system-prompt \"{agent_prompt}\" \\\n  -p \"{task_body}\"\n```\n- Current directory: job_dir\n- Inherits stderr for debugging\n- Stdout piped for event capture\n\n**MCP Configuration** (`mcp_config.rs`):\nWrites config file in job_dir based on LLM host type:\n\nFor Claude Code (.mcp.json):\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"agent-farm\": {\n      \"command\": \"/usr/local/bin/agent-farm-mcp\",\n      \"args\": [],\n      \"env\": {\n        \"AGENT_FARM_API_URL\": \"...\",\n        \"AGENT_FARM_TOKEN_ENDPOINT\": \"http://localhost:PORT/token\",\n        \"AGENT_FARM_TOKEN_SECRET\": \"...\",\n        \"AGENT_FARM_TASK_ID\": \"...\",\n        \"AGENT_FARM_ROOT_TASK_ID\": \"...\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFor Cursor CLI (.cursor-mcp.json):\n```json\n{\n  \"mcp\": {\n    \"servers\": {\n      \"agent-farm\": { ... }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Token Management** (`token.rs`):\n- TokenManager holds current token in RwLock\n- Provides `get_token()` for sync reads\n- Refreshes via `/internal/instances/{instance_id}/refresh-token`\n- Runs periodic refresh loop\n\n**Token Server** (`token_endpoint.rs`):\n- Simple Axum server on localhost:0\n- GET /token endpoint\n- Requires Bearer auth header with token_secret\n- Returns: `{\"instance_token\": \"...\"}`\n- Used by MCP server to fetch current token\n\n**Heartbeat** (`heartbeat.rs`):\n- POSTs to `/internal/instances/{instance_id}/heartbeat`\n- Payload: `{\"timestamp\": \"2024-...\", \"status\": \"running\"}`\n- Runs every `heartbeat_interval_secs` (min 1 second)\n- Logs failures but continues\n\n---\n\n### 4. docker-compose.yml and docker-compose.test.yml\n\n**Production docker-compose.yml**:\n```yaml\nservices:\n  api:\n    build:\n      context: .\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile\n    ports:\n      - \"${AGENT_FARM_PORT:-8080}:${AGENT_FARM_PORT:-8080}\"\n    environment:\n      DATABASE_URL: \"postgres://agentfarm:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD:-agentfarm}@db:5432/agentfarm\"\n      AGENT_FARM_PORT: \"${AGENT_FARM_PORT:-8080}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_BASE_URL: \"${AGENT_FARM_BASE_URL:-http://localhost:8080}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_ENCRYPTION_KEY: \"${AGENT_FARM_ENCRYPTION_KEY}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY: \"${AGENT_FARM_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY: \"${AGENT_FARM_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_CORS_ORIGINS: \"${AGENT_FARM_CORS_ORIGINS:-}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_MAX_CONCURRENT_INSTANCES: \"${AGENT_FARM_MAX_CONCURRENT_INSTANCES:-20}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_JOB_DIR_ROOT: \"${AGENT_FARM_JOB_DIR_ROOT:-/data/jobs}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_LOG_RETENTION_DAYS: \"${AGENT_FARM_LOG_RETENTION_DAYS:-30}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_LOG_LEVEL: \"${AGENT_FARM_LOG_LEVEL:-info}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_HOST_WRAPPER_BIN: \"/usr/local/bin/host-wrapper\"\n      AGENT_FARM_MCP_SERVER_BIN: \"/usr/local/bin/agent-farm-mcp\"\n      AGENT_FARM_CLAUDE_CODE_BIN: \"${AGENT_FARM_CLAUDE_CODE_BIN:-}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_CURSOR_CLI_BIN: \"${AGENT_FARM_CURSOR_CLI_BIN:-}\"\n      GITHUB_CLIENT_ID: \"${GITHUB_CLIENT_ID:-}\"\n      GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET: \"${GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET:-}\"\n      GITLAB_CLIENT_ID: \"${GITLAB_CLIENT_ID:-}\"\n      GITLAB_CLIENT_SECRET: \"${GITLAB_CLIENT_SECRET:-}\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"${AGENT_FARM_JOB_DIR_ROOT:-/data/jobs}:/data/jobs\"\n    depends_on:\n      db:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD\", \"curl\", \"-sf\", \"http://localhost:${AGENT_FARM_PORT:-8080}/health\"]\n      interval: 10s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 5\n      start_period: 30s\n\n  db:\n    image: postgres:16-alpine\n    environment:\n      POSTGRES_USER: agentfarm\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: \"${POSTGRES_PASSWORD:-agentfarm}\"\n      POSTGRES_DB: agentfarm\n    ports:\n      - \"${AGENT_FARM_DB_PORT:-5432}:5432\"\n    volumes:\n      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"pg_isready -U agentfarm\"]\n      interval: 5s\n      timeout: 3s\n      retries: 5\n    restart: unless-stopped\n\nvolumes:\n  pgdata:\n```\n\n**Test Override (docker-compose.test.yml)**:\n```yaml\nservices:\n  api:\n    environment:\n      AGENT_FARM_PORT: \"${AF_TEST_PORT:-18081}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_BASE_URL: \"http://localhost:${AF_TEST_PORT:-18081}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_JOB_DIR_ROOT: \"${AF_TEST_JOB_DIR:-/tmp/af-test/jobs}\"\n      DATABASE_URL: \"postgres://agentfarm:agentfarm@db:5432/agentfarm\"\n      AGENT_FARM_MAX_CONCURRENT_INSTANCES: \"5\"\n      AGENT_FARM_LOG_LEVEL: \"debug\"\n      AGENT_FARM_ENCRYPTION_KEY: \"${AF_TEST_ENCRYPTION_KEY}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY: \"${AF_TEST_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY: \"${AF_TEST_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY}\"\n      AGENT_FARM_CLAUDE_CODE_BIN: \"/usr/local/bin/mock-agent\"\n      GITHUB_CLIENT_ID: \"test-github-client\"\n      GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET: \"test-github-secret\"\n    ports:\n      - \"${AF_TEST_PORT:-18081}:${AF_TEST_PORT:-18081}\"\n    volumes: !reset\n      - \"${AF_TEST_JOB_DIR:-/tmp/af-test/jobs}:${AF_TEST_JOB_DIR:-/tmp/af-test/jobs}\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD\", \"curl\", \"-sf\", \"http://localhost:${AF_TEST_PORT:-18081}/health\"]\n      interval: 10s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 5\n      start_period: 30s\n\n  db:\n    ports:\n      - \"${AF_TEST_DB_PORT:-15433}:5432\"\n    volumes: !reset []\n    tmpfs:\n      - /var/lib/postgresql/data\n```\n\n**Key Differences in Tests**:\n- Separate port range (18080+)\n- Separate DB port range (15432+)\n- Job directory in /tmp/af-test-{INSTANCE_ID}/jobs\n- Max 5 concurrent instances\n- Debug logging\n- Uses mock-agent instead of real Claude Code\n- In-memory DB (tmpfs)\n\n---\n\n### 5. scripts/ci-instance.sh - How It Works\n\nComplete script that manages test instance lifecycle:\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nACTION=\"${1:?Usage: ci-instance.sh <up|down|wait> <instance-id>}\"\nINSTANCE_ID=\"${2:?Usage: ci-instance.sh <up|down|wait> <instance-id>}\"\n\nPROJECT=\"agent-farm-test-${INSTANCE_ID}\"\nPORT=$((18080 + INSTANCE_ID))\nDB_PORT=$((15432 + INSTANCE_ID))\nJOB_DIR=\"/tmp/af-test-${INSTANCE_ID}/jobs\"\n\nexport AF_TEST_PORT=\"${PORT}\"\nexport AF_TEST_DB_PORT=\"${DB_PORT}\"\nexport AF_TEST_JOB_DIR=\"${JOB_DIR}\"\n\n# Generate test-only crypto keys if not already set.\nif [ -z \"${AF_TEST_ENCRYPTION_KEY:-}\" ]; then\n  export AF_TEST_ENCRYPTION_KEY=\"$(openssl rand -base64 32)\"\nfi\nif [ -z \"${AF_TEST_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY:-}\" ]; then\n  key_tmp_dir=\"$(mktemp -d)\"\n  openssl genrsa -out \"${key_tmp_dir}/private.pem\" 2048 2>/dev/null\n  openssl rsa -in \"${key_tmp_dir}/private.pem\" -pubout -out \"${key_tmp_dir}/public.pem\" 2>/dev/null\n  export AF_TEST_JWT_PRIVATE_KEY=\"$(<\"${key_tmp_dir}/private.pem\")\"\n  export AF_TEST_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY=\"$(<\"${key_tmp_dir}/public.pem\")\"\n  rm -rf \"${key_tmp_dir}\"\nfi\n\nCOMPOSE=\"docker compose -p ${PROJECT} -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.test.yml\"\n\ncase \"${ACTION}\" in\n  up)\n    mkdir -p \"${JOB_DIR}\"\n    ${COMPOSE} up -d --build --wait\n    echo \"Test instance ${INSTANCE_ID} ready on port ${PORT}\"\n    ;;\n  down)\n    ${COMPOSE} down -v --remove-orphans\n    rm -rf \"/tmp/af-test-${INSTANCE_ID}\"\n    echo \"Test instance ${INSTANCE_ID} torn down\"\n    ;;\n  wait)\n    for i in $(seq 1 60); do\n      if curl -sf \"http://localhost:${PORT}/health\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n        echo \"Test instance ${INSTANCE_ID} healthy\"\n        exit 0\n      fi\n      sleep 1\n    done\n    echo \"Test instance ${INSTANCE_ID} failed to become healthy\" >&2\n    exit 1\n    ;;\n  *)\n    echo \"Unknown action: ${ACTION}\" >&2\n    exit 1\n    ;;\nesac\n```\n\n**How It Works**:\n\n1. **Parsing**: Takes ACTION (up/down/wait) and INSTANCE_ID (numeric)\n2. **Port Calculation**: Derives unique ports based on instance ID\n3. **Crypto Key Generation**: Creates RSA keys and encryption secret if not provided\n4. **Docker Compose**: Runs compose with unique project name per instance\n5. **Three Actions**:\n   - `up`: Creates job dir, builds and starts containers, waits for readiness\n   - `down`: Stops containers, removes volumes, cleans up temp files\n   - `wait`: Polls /health endpoint for 60 seconds\n\n---\n\n### 6. crates/scheduler/ - Core Scheduling & Concurrency Logic\n\n**Main Scheduler Trait** (`trait.rs`):\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait Scheduler: Send + Sync {\n    async fn start_instance(&self, request: StartInstanceRequest) -> Result<InstanceHandle, SchedulerError>;\n    async fn stop_instance(&self, instance_id: Uuid) -> Result<(), SchedulerError>;\n    async fn commit_and_push(&self, request: CommitPushRequest) -> Result<CommitPushResult, SchedulerError>;\n    async fn cleanup_job_dir(&self, job_dir: &str) -> Result<(), SchedulerError>;\n    fn active_instances(&self) -> u32;\n    fn status_label(&self) -> &'static str;\n}\n```\n\n**LocalScheduler Implementation** (`local.rs`):\n\nInitialization:\n```rust\npub fn new(config: SchedulerConfig, jwt_keys: Arc<JwtKeys>) -> Self {\n    let concurrency_manager = Arc::new(ConcurrencyManager::new(config.platform_max_instances));\n    concurrency_manager.clone().dequeue_loop();  // Spawn dequeue background task\n    let deferred_cleanup = DeferredCleanupManager::new();\n    deferred_cleanup.start();\n    InstanceTimeoutMonitor::start(concurrency_manager.clone(), config.graceful_shutdown_timeout);\n    Self { config, concurrency_manager, deferred_cleanup, jwt_keys }\n}\n```\n\n**StartInstance Flow**:\n1. Create/validate job directory (or use provided one)\n2. Shallow clone repo into job_dir\n3. Generate JWT instance token with timeout\n4. Generate shared secret for token endpoint\n5. Try to acquire concurrency slot:\n   - If available: register instance immediately\n   - If not available: enqueue in pending queue, wait for notification\n6. Setup git credentials in job_dir\n7. Spawn host-wrapper process with environment variables\n8. Register InstanceInfo with concurrency manager\n\n**Concurrency Manager** (`concurrency.rs`):\n\n```rust\npub struct ConcurrencyManager {\n    pub platform_max: u32,\n    pub running_instances: DashMap<Uuid, InstanceInfo>,\n    pub team_counts: DashMap<Uuid, u32>,\n    pub pending_queue: Arc<Mutex<VecDeque<PendingInstance>>>,\n}\n```\n\nKey methods:\n- `try_acquire(team_id, team_max)`: Returns true if can start (respects platform_max and team limits)\n- `register(info)`: Adds to running_instances, increments team_counts\n- `release(instance_id)`: Removes from running, decrements team_counts, tries_drain_one()\n- `enqueue(pending)`: Adds to pending_queue\n- `dequeue_loop()`: Spawns background task that polls pending_queue every 250ms, drains when slots available\n\n**Instance Timeout Monitoring** (`timeout.rs`):\n```rust\npub struct InstanceTimeoutMonitor;\n\nimpl InstanceTimeoutMonitor {\n    pub fn start(concurrency_manager: Arc<ConcurrencyManager>, graceful_shutdown_timeout: Duration) {\n        tokio::spawn(async move {\n            let mut interval = tokio::time::interval(Duration::from_secs(10));\n            loop {\n                interval.tick().await;\n                // Find timed-out instances\n                let mut timed_out = Vec::new();\n                for item in concurrency_manager.running_instances.iter() {\n                    if item.started_at.elapsed() >= Duration::from_secs(item.timeout_seconds as u64) {\n                        timed_out.push(*item.key());\n                    }\n                }\n                // Kill them gracefully\n                for instance_id in timed_out {\n                    if let Some(entry) = concurrency_manager.running_instances.get(&instance_id) {\n                        let proc = entry.process_handle.clone();\n                        let mut g = proc.lock().await;\n                        if let Some(child) = g.as_mut() {\n                            let _ = child.start_kill();\n                            let _ = tokio::time::timeout(graceful_shutdown_timeout, child.wait()).await;\n                        }\n                    }\n                    concurrency_manager.release(instance_id).await;\n                }\n            }\n        });\n    }\n}\n```\n- Runs every 10 seconds\n- Checks if any running instance exceeded timeout_seconds\n- Sends SIGTERM, waits up to graceful_shutdown_timeout\n- Releases the slot\n\n**Environment Variables Passed to Host Wrapper** (`spawn.rs`):\n\n```rust\npub fn build_spawn_env(request: &StartInstanceRequest, job_dir: &str, config: &SchedulerConfig) -> Vec<(String, String)> {\n    vec![\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_API_URL\", config.api_base_url.clone()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_INSTANCE_ID\", request.instance_id.to_string()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_INSTANCE_TOKEN\", request.mcp_server_config.instance_token.clone()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_INSTANCE_TIMEOUT\", request.instance_timeout_seconds.to_string()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_TOKEN_SECRET\", request.mcp_server_config.token_secret.clone()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_TASK_ID\", request.task_id.to_string()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_ROOT_TASK_ID\", request.root_task_id.to_string()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_LLM_HOST\", serde_json::to_string(&request.agent_snapshot.llm_host)...),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_LLM_HOST_BIN\", llm_bin),  // From config\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_MCP_SERVER_BIN\", config.mcp_server_bin.clone()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_JOB_DIR\", job_dir.to_string()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL\", config.heartbeat_interval_secs.to_string()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_GRACEFUL_SHUTDOWN_TIMEOUT\", config.graceful_shutdown_timeout.as_secs()...),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_SYSTEM_PROMPT\", request.system_prompt.clone()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_AGENT_PROMPT\", request.agent_snapshot.agent_prompt.clone()),\n        (\"AGENT_FARM_TASK_BODY\", request.task_body.clone()),\n        (llm_key_var, request.llm_api_key.clone()),  // ANTHROPIC_API_KEY or OPENAI_API_KEY\n    ]\n}\n```\n\n**Job Directory Setup** (`job_dir.rs`):\n- Creates unique directory under job_dir_root with pattern: `{root_task_id}/...`\n- Shallow clones git repo into it\n- Sets up git credentials\n- Current working directory for all child processes\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Summary\n\nThe agent_farm system follows this execution flow:\n\n1. **API Server** receives request to execute task → calls Scheduler.start_instance()\n2. **Scheduler** acquires concurrency slot, creates job directory, generates tokens\n3. **Scheduler** spawns **host-wrapper** with environment variables and job directory\n4. **Host-wrapper** starts:\n   - Token server (localhost:0 for MCP token fetches)\n   - Writes MCP config file (.mcp.json) to job directory\n   - Spawns LLM host binary (claude code or cursor cli)\n   - Captures stdout/stderr events\n   - Runs heartbeat loop, token refresh, log flush\n5. **LLM Host** (claude code/cursor cli):\n   - Reads .mcp.json configuration\n   - Spawns **MCP Server** as subprocess\n   - Sends task_body as prompt\n   - Can call tools: complete_task, fail_task, get_task_context, query_logs\n6. **Mock Agent** (in tests) acts as LLM host:\n   - Configurable behavior via environment variables\n   - Can c