{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vjf8XxSAHfaj5fxmXJhvoZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information you need. Let me compile a comprehensive report of the API contracts:\n\n## Complete API Contract Report\n\n### 1. Router Organization (`crates/api-server/src/router.rs`)\n\nThe application uses Axum and is structured as follows:\n- **Health check**: `/health` (GET)\n- **API v1 routes** at `/api/v1`:\n  - `/openapi.json` - OpenAPI spec\n  - `/auth/*` - Authentication routes\n  - `/users/*` - User management\n  - `/agents/*` - Agent management\n  - `/teams/*` - Team management, inboxes, snapshots, DLQ, team-scoped tasks/jobs\n  - `/tasks/*` - Task management (global and team-scoped)\n  - `/jobs/*` - Job management (global and team-scoped)\n  - `/credentials/*` - Credentials management\n  - `/logs/*` - Logs (with rate limiting)\n  - `/admin/*` - Admin routes\n  - `/events/*` - SSE event streaming (merged at root)\n- **Internal routes** at `/internal` - Host wrapper callbacks\n- **Static HTML pages**: `/auth/cli/:device_code` and `/credentials/cli/:device_code`\n\nAll routes have CORS, rate limiting, request ID tracking, and client ID middleware applied.\n\n---\n\n### 2. SSE Event Implementation (`crates/api-server/src/routes/events.rs`)\n\n**Event Types Sent** (mapped to SSE event names):\n```\nPlatformEvent::TaskStatusChanged -> \"task_status_changed\"\nPlatformEvent::TaskCreated -> \"task_created\"\nPlatformEvent::TaskRouted -> \"task_routed\"\nPlatformEvent::InstanceStarted -> \"instance_started\"\nPlatformEvent::InstanceExited -> \"instance_exited\"\nPlatformEvent::Heartbeat -> \"heartbeat\"\nPlatformEvent::DlqAddition -> \"dlq_addition\"\nPlatformEvent::JobCompleted -> \"job_completed\"\nPlatformEvent::LogEntry -> \"log_entry\"\n```\n\n**Event Format**:\n- `SseEvent` with:\n  - `id`: `env.id` (u64 converted to string)\n  - `event`: event type name (string)\n  - `data`: JSO